changes.value:
swissarmyhammer-tools/src/mcp/tools/shell/mod.rs (lines 143-170)

Every arm in the `match op_str` block uses an explicit `return`, making the match a statement rather than an expression:
```rust
match op_str {
    "execute command" | "" => {
        return execute_command::execute_execute_command(...).await;
    }
    ...
    other => {
        return Err(McpError::invalid_params(...));
    }
}
```

Since the match is the last statement in the function and every arm returns, this should be written as a match expression without `return`:
```rust
match op_str {
    "execute command" | "" => execute_command::execute_execute_command(...).await,
    ...
    other => Err(McpError::invalid_params(...)),
}
```

Suggestion: Remove redundant `return` keywords and use the match as an expression. This is idiomatic Rust per Clippy's `needless_return` lint."

